defaultShihab Uddin Ahamaddefault: My understanding of the civil society that I have been engaging with since 2006 is that, in 
defaultBurma
default, civil society is highly biased.  They are politically biased, religiously biased and ethnically biased.  When you try to engage with them, since their history is that civil society was not much encouraged by the Government, you only have one way to work: with the religious institutions.  Many are from the church.  It is difficult to encourage church
default&#x2011;
